events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Erik Spoelstra remained perfect on Christmas, and a record-tying show from Duncan Robinson helped him stay that way.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spoelstra stays perfect on Christmas, Heat beat Pels 111-98

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton scored 31 points and the Milwaukee Bucks routed the Golden State Warriors 138-99 on Friday to win their first Christmas Day home game in over half a century.
headlines.shortLinkText: Middleton scores 31 as Bucks trounce Warriors 138-99

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 37 points with eight assists in his return to Boston and Kevin Durant added 29 for Brooklyn on Friday to lead the Nets to a 123-95 victory over the Celtics.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving scores 37, leads Nets to 123-95 win over Celtics

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 28 points and LeBron James had 22 while becoming the second-leading Christmas scorer in NBA history during the Los Angeles Lakers' 138-115 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron becomes No. 2 Xmas scorer, Lakers top Mavs 138-115

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard had 21 points before taking an elbow to the face in the fourth quarter, Paul George scored 23 points and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Denver Nuggets 121-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard leaves bloodied, but Clippers beat Nuggets 121-108
